	<Title>
		Working out? Time your meals right
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;When you work out after a big meal, you may feel sluggish or have cramps or an upset stomach. That&apos;s because your muscles and your digestive system are competing with each other for energy. On the flip side, if you don&apos;t eat before you exercise, especially right away in the morning, you may feel weak, faint or tired. To strike the right balance, eat a light snack before exercising. After a big meal, wait a few hours before hitting the gym.&lt;/p&gt;
